title: 820-00165 no power a1466
message:
So missing PM_SLP_SUS_L, no reason to search for S3/0 voltages.

Check S5_PWRGD, PM_DSW_PWRGD, PCH_DSWVRMEN, PM_BATLOW_L and all PCH's RTC signals.

title: 820-00165 no power a1466
message:
This looks like PCH issue.
Put quality flux and heat it, in case of accumalated crap underneath.
180-200 degrees for 15-20s is good enough; you don't need to melt the balls.
You can heat entire CPU, but PCH area is the target there.
